Name: Hoya 58mm HMC ND4 Multi-Coated Neutral Density Filter + Accessory Kit for Canon, Nikon, Sony, Olympus & Pentax Lenses
Long Description: Kit Includes 4 Items with all Manufacturer-supplied Accessories + Full USA Warranties: 1) Hoya 58mm HMC Neutral Density ND4 Multi-Coated Glass Filter 2) Lenspen NLP-1C Lens Pen Cleaning System 3) CapKeeper 2 4) Precision Design 6-Piece Camera + Lens Cleaning Kit This Hoya Multi-Coated Neutral Density (ND) Filter is an essential accessory for any photographers camera bag. ND filters reduce the amount of visible light that enters the lens, allowing the user to utilize wider apertures or slower shutter speeds, particularly in bright conditions. ND filters work especially well for portraits by allowing the photographer to reduce the depth of field, producing pleasant background blur while keeping the subject in sharp focus. These filters are also often used to emphasize movement by permitting slow shutter speeds in bright light, giving life to photos that would otherwise look frozen in time. This particular filter (HMC) is multi-coated to minimize reflection on the filter surface, which reduces flare and ghosting, and produces sharp contrast and well-balanced color. An ND4 filter reduces the amount of light by 2 stops. When to use a Neutral Density Filter: To enable slow shutter speeds to be used to record movement in subjects such as waterfalls, clouds, cars, etc. To decrease depth of field by allowing wider apertures to be used, which helps separate subjects from their background. To decrease the effective ISO of high speed film (ie: above ISO400) and allow it to be used outdoors in bright situations. To allow video cameras (which have fixed shutter speeds) to film subjects such as snow, sand or other bright scenes which would normally cause overexposure.
Short Description: Hoya 58mm HMC ND4 Multi-Coated Neutral Density Filter + Accessory Kit for Canon, Nikon, Sony, Olympus & Pentax Lenses

Our Hypericum extract is synergistically blended with premium quality, whole St. John s Wort herb in the perfect balance to ensure consistent hypericin content in each capsule. St. John s Wort, or Hypericum perforatum , is a perennial plant which grows on sunlit hillsides and forest edges. Its attractive yellow flowers release a blood-red juice when crushed. They bloom from June until August and are considered to be most potent during the flowering season, particularly on St. John s Day . This may account for its traditional historical uses.

Name: Whisker CityA Guillotine Pet Nail Clipper
Long Description: Trim nails every 4-6 weeks. After trimming nails, gently smooth rough edges with a nail file. file only in one direction from the top of the nail downward. Made exclusively for PetSmart. Directions: Hold your pet's foot and gently push down with your thumb at the base of the nail. This will cause the nail to extend slightly, making it easier for you to see the nail. Trim the nail at a 45-degree angle so that the newly cut nail is flush with the floor when you pet walks. There is a blood vessel, in each nail, called the quick. Do not cut the nail so short that you cut the quick. Always cut just the excess nail. The pinkish color of the quick is easy to see in pets with light-colored nails. However, it is almost impossible to see on cats with dark nails. To avoid cutting the quick, locate it from the underside of each nail before you begin cutting. Cut each nail back just a little at a time until you get close, but no right up to the quick. If you do inadvertently cut the quick, apply pressure to stop bleeding.

Long Description: The SENTRY Clean Up Ultra + pheromones Stain & Odor Remover is a professional strength formula with extra enzymes to rapidly remove organic pet messes such as urine, vomit, blood and feces, in addition to pheromone technology proven to modify behaviors such as inappropriate marking. Two exclusive odor control technologies (Extreme Odor Control and Odor Suppression Technology) trap and destroy odors. Features: Lavender fields scent Used For: Removes stains in 5 minutes Weight: 32 fl oz / 945 mL Caution: Product may irritate eyes. Avoid eye contact. In case of contact, flush with water. As with all cleaning products, keep out of reach of children and pets. Directions: Before using: Remove excess solid or liquid waste. Shake bottle well and test for colorfastness on a hidden area. Do not use on wool or leather surfaces. Use the brush feature: Brush on bottom can be used as attached to bottle (remove base cover and use in a circular motion) or as a separate hand-held brush (remove base cover and brush, assemble brush piece). Treating the stain: 1. Treat - Saturate the stain (including carpet, backing and padding) covering twice the size of the area. 2. Brush - Brush in circular motion over the stained area to break apart matted carpet. 3. Wait - Wait 10 minutes, then blot with color-safe cloth. 4. Dry - Let the area dry naturally 24-48 hours. When dry, the stain and odor will be gone. If it dries and you can still smell the odor, the area was not completely saturated. Repeat steps above, thoroughly saturating the area. Ingredients: Water, Microbiological Concentrate, Polysorbate 80, Fragrance, Odor Modifier Complex, Pheromone

Name: Corby Spirit And Wine Limited Gooderham And Worts
Long Description: Gooderham & Worts Four Grain whisky is an homage to the original Toronto distillery, founded in 1832, Gooderham & Worts. James Worts and his brother-in-law, William Gooderham became successful millers after their arrival to Canada from the UK. A distillery was later added as wheat production began to increase in Upper Canada. Distillation was an efficient way to preserve excess grain that was prone to spoilage, as well as dispose of the grain middlings left over from the milling process. After taking out a patent for a “Riley still”, Gooderham & Worts would fundamentally change distilling in Canada by double distilling whisky through 2 columns making a softer whisky than what was available at the time. By the late 1800’s Toronto’s Gooderham & Worts distillery was the largest in the world. Under the guidance of Doctor Don Livermore, a new Gooderham & Worts Four Grain whisky was launched as a tribute to the original recipe from 1832.
Short Description: It is a premium blend of four diverse grains – corn, wheat, barley and rye. All four grains are distilled and aged separately before blended, comprised of pot and column distilled wheat, barley and rye, and double column distilled corn. 100% locally sourced grain from Ontario Canada, aged in a combination of new virgin oak casks and used Bourbon casks. Distilled true to the tradition started Gooderham & Worts started in 1832. 44. 4% ABV
